beer.beer_description: Named after one of our favourite beaches along the 90-Mile stretch in Gippsland. This Pale Ale is a super-reliable everyday drinker that ticks all the boxes. Double dry hopped with Eclipse & Vic Secret giving it waves of flavour for days, it combines rounded tropical fruit notes with a smooth, juicy finish and low bitterness.

items.badge_description: It takes the perfect amount of light, the right framing and a touch of creative love to get the perfect picture of your brew. Now it’s time to drink it! That's 435 check-ins with a photo.  Try 5 more for Level 88!

beer.beer_description:
Icy, Bold, Cold, Hoppy & super refreshing. 

Hops: Simcoe, Idaho7, Moteeka, Nelson Sauvin, Mosaic

Yeast: W34/70

Malt: Voyager - Compass, Chit & Wheat

Aroma: Bursts of fresh lime, tangerine & mango 

Body: Balanced bitterness, with a crisp & satisfying finish

items.badge_description: Put down those cases of Ale Yeast because unlike other IPA styles, the Cold IPA and IPL are brewed with Lager Yeast and a generous amount of hops. When you want a punch of hops with a lighter finish, reach for a Cold IPA or India Pale Lager. That's 5 different beers with the style of IPA - Cold or Lager - IPL (India Pale Lager). Try 5 more or Level 2!

items.checkin_comment: "Brewed with a double dose of hazelnuts and freshly roasted coffee. Finished off with ripe bananas. Contains lactose."  Sounds like a winner. Somehow misses the mark.  Little bit bananary, bit sweet, bit lacking the rest.

beer.beer_description:
Ready to go Bananas? A tantalising milk stout brewed with a double dose of hazelnut and freshly roasted coffee from our good friends at Fat Cat Coffee Roasters. Finished off with ripe Aussie bananas, it's a creamy breakfast coffee shaken up with a dreamy nutty dessert, and a banana on top.

Contains: Lactose, Nuts, and Coffee

user.bio: Currently in search of world's the dankest IPA

beer.beer_description:
Paradisio is the ultimate old school meets new world West Coast IPA with a big, bold malty backbone by a super fresh blend of classic and new American hops

It’s Paradise in a can. 

Brewed in Traralgon

items.badge_description: While spontaneity can be fun, sometimes you want to make sure your adventure will rock. Checkout the menu at an Untappd Verified Venue before visiting and know exactly what’s on tap! That's 170 check-ins at venue that is verified. Try 5 more for Level 35!

beer.beer_description:
The result of an exciting collaboration between Good Land Brewing (AUS)
& Stewart Brewing (SCOT). We have both brewed the exact same beer
using the same blend of Australian
& UK Hops, the only difference being local malt. 
Expect grapefruit, Mango & Passionfruit aromas, with a nice clean and slightly sweet flavour profile.
Cheers to this global beer adventure!

CONTAINS LACTOSE.

Brewed in Traralgon

items.badge_description: What happens when you take two or more amazing breweries, throw them into the tank and let them ferment together? An amazing collaboration beer, that’s what! Cheers to working together to create the perfect flavor. That's 45 different beers that have been brewed as a collaboration. Try 5 more for Level 10!

beer.beer_description:
Kerfuffle is our lactose sour base, conditioned on blueberry, strawberry, lime pink marshmallows and soft serve vanilla ice cream.
CONTAINS LACTOSE

Brewed in Traralgon

beer.beer_description:
Our Fresh Raspberry Edition!

We started off with a light peat smoked malt base & graham crackers in the mash, we then left this big stout to age in ex buffalo trace barrels before being conditioned on chocolate, marshmallows, milk sugar, vanilla beans & layers and layers of fresh raspberry.

Brewed in Traralgon.

items.badge_description: When a single isn’t enough, make it a double. Doubling the hops and malts in a recipe results in a higher ABV and can pack quite a boozey punch. That's 355 different beers with the style that contains Imperial / Double in its style name. Try 5 more for Level 72!

items.checkin_comment: Head dissipated quickly. Moderate body. Mild banana in the aroma. A little nutty and banana in the flavour. Kinda has breakfast smoothie vibes

If ye be seekin' flavours of molasses, toffee, rum, and dark fries, arr - you've come to the proper place!

items.checkin_comment: Only subtly different to the green star. Maybe a little less piney and a little more bitter? Not sure both are a pretty good drop.

beer.beer_description:
Introducing Gold Star, a tribute to the warm, vibrant spirit of South Texas. This amber lager shines with a deep, amber hue and a smooth, rich flavour profile.

Brewed in Traralgon

PUT YOUR 3-D GLASSES ON!!!!
Step right up and prepare for a taste sensation like no other this canvent season with Amusement Park.
This extraordinary IPA blends the sweetness of real fairy floss and Tahitian vanilla beans, with the hoppy goodness of Citra, Idaho7 & Mosaic.

Brewed & Canned in Traralgon

The Pud starts with a rich caramel base slowly opening up to toffee, molasses and dark fruit notes then finishing with a beautifully balanced hop bitterness, producing a remarkably complex and palate pleasing beer.
Mmmmmm..... THE PUD

Reassuringly smooth, Man on the Moon is brewed with cacao, vanilla and lactose to create a rich, full-flavoured milk Stout that's smooth and remarkably easy-drinking. The creamy roast, soft palate and easy sweetness make this stout as soothing and softly contoured as the Moon's surface itself.

Brewed In Traralgon

This White IPA was created with style, to go down with ease. A blend of two distinct beer styles, Belgian Wit and an American IPA. Pumped up with a huge dry hop of Citra, Mosaic, and HBC 586 for a spicy yet citrusy summer taste.

Indies Champion Speciality Beer 2022

Gezellig showcases the rich
'chocolate, caramel and roasted
{notes of this beautiful style,
"while also providing the needed
roundness and integration of the
bourbon and oak characteristics
to produce a warm and cosy
experience. Brewed and packaged
for our first-year anniversary.

A Good Land x Carwin Cellars collab
telebrating our first birthday. Oak
aged in white wine barrels then lighty
di-hopped. Packaged unfiltered, the
baer has a robust body, slight acidity,
and a touch of toasted oak character;
with layers of honey, a touch of malty
sweetness and slight wisps of white
wine. German hops balance the malt
with a crisp bitter finish. Refreshing,
elegant and refined.

Named after one of our favourite beaches along the 90-Mile stretch in Gippsland. This Pale Ale is a super-reliable everyday drinker that ticks all the boxes. Double dry hopped with Eclipse & Vic Secret giving it waves of flavour for days, it combines rounded tropical fruit notes with a smooth, juicy finish and low bitterness.

HEAVEN

BBBIS - Bourbon Barrel-aged Belgian Imperial Stout

Aged in Heaven Hill Barrels

Brewed and packed in Traralgon

Just imagine a beer dowsed in raspberry, covered in cream and then dipped in vanilla.

It’s a beer that delivers huge aromas of sweet raspberry and vanilla and drinks with a fully body and creamy tartness.
It’s pours a hazy pink and will leave you refreshed and craving more.
A Collab with 2 Crows Brewing, Canada

A crazy amount of fruit went into create what is our take on a Banana Pina Colada in a the form of a fresh smoothie style sour. 

Bananarama Pina Colada starts off with our super smoothie base then we loaded it with BANANA, COCONUT, freshly squeezed LIMES, PINEAPPLE, creamy creamy MILK SUGAR, plus real vanilla for a super cool and super thic Pina Colada finish.

CONTAINS LACTOSE.

Fruit: Banana, Coconut Cream, lemon & Pineapple

This is our barrel aged edition of Jazeker, aged in ex Buffalo Trace barrels and conditioned on a blend of coffee beans roasted by our mates at Fat Cat Coffee Roasters. We then threw in some thick as vanilla beans for good measure.

Indies Gold Medal Winner for best Marzen 2022

This strong amber German lager is an ode to the big beer halls in Oktoberfest Munich where we long to be.
A soft malty ever so sweet backbone with a balance of clean hop bitterness and a great long lasting off-white head.

Get your dirndl's & lederhosen on, stand on the tables, eat a pretzel and drink a Good Land beer!
PROOST!

Although man was first on the moon, we here at Good Land believe it will be a Woman on Mars.
We've brewed this red IPA with a proprietary blend of hops chosen by the Pink Boots Society, Expect big floral, citrus, tropical, and stone fruit aromas, backed up by this beautiful red malty base.

This is Good Lager. Brewed for everyday moments, a new world german style Pilsner with delicate aromas from Australian Enigma hops & fermented at a cool temperature leaving it with a bright taste and crisp finish.
It’s refreshlingly smooth and brewed with pride in Gippsland. Drink Cold. Drink Fresh. Drink Good Land Lagwe

Bringing you the memories of camping adventures to you in a can.
We started off with a lighty peat smoked malt base and then left this big stout to age in ex Buffalo Trace Bourbon barrels.
Conditioned on chocolate, marshmallows, milk sugar, Graham crackers and vanilla beans for a real campfire S’mores finish.

It’s a classic mega hazy East Coast banger! We’ve played with a couple of different dryhopping techniques to bring out a bold, juicy and intensely aromatic beer featuring Citra Lupomax, Columbus and the new experimental HBC 630 in a 20 g/L dry hop.

A hazy, juicy, unfiltered IPA.
Bursting at the seams with profuse amounts of Citra, Kohatu and Galaxy, it's a full on blast of tropical aromas. With wave after wave of juicy hop flavour, you'll find yourself on a tiki island voyage in a tropical juice breeze

Brewed in Traralgon

Cosmic Juice is a juicy and refreshing Pacific style IPA that will transport you to another dimension. Bursting with tropical fruit flavours and a bright citrus finish. Brewed with a huge a mount of Galaxy and just a touch of Aussie Cascade it literally jumps out of the can at you.
Peaty Smokey Goodness

A truly great expression of Kiwi grown hops in an everyday Hazy Pale.

Hops: Superdelic, Nelson Sauvin & Motueka 

Yeast: London Fog

Malt: Voyager - Atlas Pilsner, Wheat & Oat Malt

Aroma: Sweet candy, crushed grapes & lime fruits

Body: Smooth, easy drinking & extra juicy


Brewed in Traralgon

Paradisio is the ultimate old school meets new world West Coast IPA with a big, bold malty backbone by a super fresh blend of classic and new American hops

It’s Paradise in a can. 

Brewed in Traralgon

Something, something, whaaaat???
Dry hopped in two stages using Centennial during fermentation and a huge charge of Citra and Citra Lupomax during conditioning.

It carries plenty of Citrus and Stone-fruit aromas up front with a long, clean, lightly resinous and bitter finish, balanced by a creamy caramel malt base

For this New England IPA we started with a pretty hefty malt bill including pale, Vienna, wheat and oat malt.

Double dry-hopped with Galaxy and Talus. It’s hop forward, full of candied citrus, tropical aromas and flavours while also letting the piney, resinous notes come through 

Brewed in Traralgon Victoria

This Hazy IPA brewed with US grown Citra and Sabro hops, is the perfect miscief-maker. It's bright citrus, ripe mango and creamy coconut notes will have you feeling like you're on a tropical vacation.
The subtle bitterness and deep hazy finish make this beer as smooth and delicious as it is refreshing. 

Brewed in Traralgon
